  <title translate="true">Planes and Mechanisms</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Planes and Mechanisms</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Interface"><text styleclass="Interface" translate="true">General Notes for Planes and Mechanisms</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Each Mechanism tab/editor is &apos;locked&apos; to the Plane. that you select to add the Mechanism.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">It is, therefore, very important to select the correct Plane for each Mechanism-Editor.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">You will notice that the Add Plane is available in the Model-Editor and each Mechanism-Editor. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="line-height:1.15;"><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">New Planes are Added by selecting these </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">source </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-weight:normal; text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">elements</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">:</text></para>
          <list id="3" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="line-height:1.15; font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box" style="line-height:1.15;"><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">Plane elements</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> - in which case the &apos;New Plane&apos; can only be </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">offset</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> from the &apos;Source Plane&apos; along the +Z-axis of the &apos;Source Plane&apos;.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box" style="line-height:1.15;"><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">Line elements</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> - in which case the Origin and +X–axis of the &apos;New Plane&apos; coincides with Origin and +X–axis of the Line. The &apos;New Plane&apos; is at an angle relative to the Mechanism Plane that the Line lies on. Also, the &apos;New Plane&apos; may move with the Line, if the Line is a child to a moving Part.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box" style="line-height:1.15;"><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">X–axis or Y–axis</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> of a Base-Part or an Added-Part in a Mechanism-Editor. The Origin and +X–axis of the New Plane will align with the Origin and positive direction of the selected X or Y–axis. The &apos;New Plane&apos; can be at an angle relative to the Mechanism Plane that the Part lies on. </text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
